Step 1: List of Required dependencies

Qt for Android
Set up Android environement
	Android NDK 
	Android SDK
	Ant
	Java(OpenJDK)

Step 2: Setting up the environment variables

Suggested configuration for .bashrc:

export ADIR=/home/android-devel
export ANDROID_NDK=$ADIR/android-ndk-r11c
export ANDROID_SDK_ROOT=$ADIR/android-sdk-linux
export Qt5_android=$ADIR/Qt5.6.0/5.6/android_armv7
export PATH=$ADIR/android-sdk-linux/platform-tools/:$PATH
export ANT=/usr/bin/ant
export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk/
export CSOUND_ROOT=/home/android-devel/csound
export CSOUND_ANDROID_ROOT=/home/android-devel/csound-android-6.07.0
export INSTALL_DIR=/home/android-devel/usr/

Step 3: build

mkdir build
cd build
../build.sh

Step 4: install it on your phone
../deploy.sh
